Cook the haggis in the microwave according to packet instructions.Bring a pan of water to the boil and cook the swede for 8-10 minutes, until softened. Drain and mash until soft. Pass through a sieve until smooth.  Season with salt and freshly ground black pepper.Slice the cooked haggis and arrange in a chefs' ring placed on a plate. Spoon the mash on top and season with salt and freshly ground black pepper. Brush the top with the beaten egg and glaze the top using a blow-torch. Remove the ring.To make the gravy, reduce the beef stock and red wine to thicken. Stir in the butter and season with salt and freshly ground black pepper. Simmer for a further few minutes to thicken further.Drizzle the gravy over the haggis to serve.